# Project Name Code of Conduct

## Introduction

We, the community behind the Project Name, are committed to providing a friendly, respectful, and inclusive environment for all participants. We value diverse perspectives and aim to create a safe space where everyone feels welcome to contribute, collaborate, and engage with the project.

## Expected Behavior

- Be respectful and considerate of others' opinions and ideas.
- Use welcoming and inclusive language, avoiding offensive or derogatory remarks.
- Be patient and understanding, especially when communicating with newcomers.
- Respect differing viewpoints and approaches to problem-solving.
- Give and receive constructive feedback in a courteous manner.

## Unacceptable Behavior

The following behaviors are considered unacceptable and will not be tolerated:

- Harassment, discrimination, or any form of offensive behavior towards others.
- Personal attacks, trolling, or insulting/derogatory comments.
- Publishing others' private information without explicit consent.
- Any behavior that creates an unwelcome or hostile environment for others.

## Reporting Guidelines

If you experience or witness any behavior that violates this code of conduct, please report it immediately. You can contact [Maintainer/Community Manager Name] at [contact email or other preferred method]. All reports will be kept confidential.

## Consequences of Violations

If a participant is found to have violated this code of conduct, appropriate actions will be taken by the project maintainers. Depending on the severity and frequency of the behavior, these actions may include:

- Verbal or written warnings.
- Temporary or permanent bans from the project's communication channels or events.
- Refusal of contributions or removal of content.

## Enforcement

All reports of code of conduct violations will be reviewed and investigated by the project maintainers. They are responsible for enforcing this code of conduct. Maintainers have the right and responsibility to remove, edit, or reject any contributions that do not comply with this code of conduct.

## Scope

This code of conduct applies to all project spaces, including but not limited to GitHub repositories, issue trackers, discussion forums, community events, and social media platforms associated with the project.

## Applicability

This code of conduct applies to all contributors, maintainers, and users participating in the Project Name community.

## Adaptation and Amendments

This code of conduct may be revised or updated from time to time. Any significant changes will be communicated to the community through appropriate channels.

## Acknowledgment

By participating in the Project Name community, you acknowledge and agree to abide by this code of conduct.

---
_This code of conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.0, available at [https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/0/code_of_conduct.html](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/0/code_of_conduct.html)_
